@startuml MatchMonitorGroupBetting_AssociationDetection
!theme plain
title Match Monitor Group Betting - Association Detection Logic

start

:Configuration: MatchDetectAssociationSettingModel;

note left
    **Class Properties:**
    + HashSet<int> DeviceSports
    + HashSet<int> AISports
    + HashSet<int> IPSports
    + HashSet<int> _3MatchesLast7DaysSports
    + HashSet<int> IPLast3DaysSports
    
    **Example Configuration:**
    From API Parameters:
    - sportsDevice = "1,2,3,4,5"
    - sportsAI = "1,2,3,4,5"
    - sportsIP = "1,2,3,4,5"
    - sports3MatchesLast7Days = "1,2,3,4,5"
    - sportsIPLast3Days = "1,2,3,4,5"
    
    Parsed to HashSets:
    - DeviceSports = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
    - AISports = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
    - IPSports = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
    
    Sport IDs: 1=Soccer, 2=Basketball, 3=Tennis, etc.
end note

:Input: Customer Lists + SportType;

note right
    **Input Parameters:**
    - ctsCustIDList: "5001,5002,5003,5004,5005"
    - custIDList: "user1,user2,user3,user4,user5"
    - licCustIDList: "lic1,lic2,lic3"
    - sportType: 1 (Soccer)
end note

:Check Sport Configuration;

note right
    SportType = 1 (Soccer)
        
        Check if Soccer uses each detection method:
        - IsDevice = DeviceSports.Contains(1)
        - IsAI = AISports.Contains(1)
        - IsIP = IPSports.Contains(1)
        - Is3MatchesLast7Days = _3MatchesLast7DaysSports.Contains(1)
        - IsIPLast3Days = IPLast3DaysSports.Contains(1)
end note

:Create DetectAssociationParamModel;

note right
    **C# Code:**
    
    private IEnumerable<DetectAssociationMergeGroupLv1Entity> 
    DetectAssociation(
        string ctsCustIDList, 
        string custIDList, 
        string licCustIDList, 
        int sportType)
    {
        var param = new DetectAssociationParamModel
        {
            CTSCustIds = ctsCustIDList,
            CustIds = custIDList,
            IsDevice = AssDetectSetting.DeviceSports.Contains(sportType),
            IsAI = AssDetectSetting.AISports.Contains(sportType),
            IsIP = AssDetectSetting.IPSports.Contains(sportType),
            Is3MatchesLast7Days = 
                AssDetectSetting._3MatchesLast7DaysSports.Contains(sportType),
            IsIPLast3Days = 
                AssDetectSetting.IPLast3DaysSports.Contains(sportType),
            CustIdsIPLast3Days = licCustIDList
        };
        
        return _associationDetection.DetectAssociationLv1(param);
    }
end note

:Call AssociationDetectionService.DetectAssociationLv1();

:Database/Service Execution;
note right
    SP: CTS_AssociationDetection_Lv1
    
    Input:
    - @CTSCustIds = "5001,5002,5003,5004,5005"
    - @CustIds = "user1,user2,user3,user4,user5"
    - @IsDevice = 1
    - @IsAI = 1
    - @IsIP = 1
    - @Is3MatchesLast7Days = 1
    - @IsIPLast3Days = 1
    - @CustIdsIPLast3Days = "lic1,lic2,lic3"
end note

partition "Detection Logic (5 Criteria)" {
    :Parse Customer IDs;
    
    if (IsDevice?) then (yes)
        :1. Device Detection;
        note right
            **Criteria:** Same DeviceID
            
            **Query:**
            SELECT CustID, DeviceID
            FROM CTSCustomer
            WHERE CustID IN (@CustIds)
            GROUP BY DeviceID
            HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
            
            **Example:**
            User1: DeviceID = "ABC123"
            User2: DeviceID = "ABC123"
            → Group them together
            
            **Use Case:**
            - Same phone/computer
            - Shared device
            - Internet cafe
        end note
    endif
    
    if (IsAI?) then (yes)
        :2. AI Detection;
        note right
            **Criteria:** ML pattern matching
            
            **Process:**
            - Analyze betting patterns
            - Calculate similarity scores
            - Group similar customers
            
            **Example:**
            - Similar betting timing
            - Similar bet amounts
            - Similar selection patterns
            
            **Use Case:**
            - Sophisticated fraud
            - Pattern-based detection
        end note
    endif
    
    if (IsIP?) then (yes)
        :3. IP Detection;
        note right
            **Criteria:** Same IP address
            
            **Query:**
            SELECT CustID, IPAddress
            FROM TicketTrans
            WHERE CustID IN (@CustIds)
                AND BetTime >= NOW() - INTERVAL 1 DAY
            GROUP BY IPAddress
            HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT CustID) > 1
            
            **Example:**
            User1: IP = "192.168.1.100"
            User2: IP = "192.168.1.100"
            → Group them together
        end note
    endif
    
    if (Is3MatchesLast7Days?) then (yes)
        :4. Co-betting (3+ matches in 7 days);
        note right
            **Criteria:** Bet together on 3+ matches
            
            **Query:**
            SELECT CustID1, CustID2, COUNT(*) as Cnt
            FROM (
                SELECT DISTINCT MatchID, CustID
                FROM TicketTrans
                WHERE CustID IN (@CustIds)
                    AND BetTime >= NOW() - INTERVAL 7 DAY
            ) t1
            JOIN t2 ON t1.MatchID = t2.MatchID
            GROUP BY CustID1, CustID2
            HAVING COUNT(*) >= 3
            
            **Example:**
            User1 & User2 both bet on:
            Match A, Match B, Match C
            → Group them together
        end note
    endif
    
    if (IsIPLast3Days?) then (yes)
        :5. IP Last 3 Days (License Customers);
        note right
            **Criteria:** Same IP in last 3 days
            
            **Query:**
            SELECT CustID, IPAddress
            FROM TicketTrans
            WHERE CustID IN (@CustIdsIPLast3Days)
                AND BetTime >= NOW() - INTERVAL 3 DAY
            GROUP BY IPAddress
            HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT CustID) > 1
            
            **Use Case:**
            - Licensed/VIP customers
            - Recent activity focus
            - Tighter time window
        end note
    endif
    
    :Merge All Detection Results;
    note right
        **Merge Logic:**
        Combine results from all methods:
        - Union of all detected groups
        - Merge overlapping groups
        - Assign final GroupID
        
        **Example Merge:**
        Device Detection: {user1, user2} → Group 1
        IP Detection: {user2, user3} → Group 2
        Merged: {user1, user2, user3} → Group 1
        
        **Merge Algorithm:**
        - If any overlap → Same group
        - Transitive grouping
    end note
    
    :Assign Association Type;
    note right
        For each customer, record which method(s)
        detected the association:
        - "Device"
        - "AI"
        - "IP"
        - "3Matches"
        - "IPLast3Days"
        - "Device,IP" (multiple)
    end note
}

:Return Detection Results;

note right
    IEnumerable<DetectAssociationMergeGroupLv1Entity>
    
    Example Output:
    [
        {
            CustID: "user1",
            CTSCustID: 5001,
            GroupID: 1,
            AssociationType: "Device",
            DeviceID: "ABC123",
            Confidence: 0.95
        },
        {
            CustID: "user2",
            CTSCustID: 5002,
            GroupID: 1,
            AssociationType: "Device,IP",
            DeviceID: "ABC123",
            IPAddress: "192.168.1.100",
            Confidence: 0.98
        },
        {
            CustID: "user3",
            CTSCustID: 5003,
            GroupID: 1,
            AssociationType: "IP",
            IPAddress: "192.168.1.100",
            Confidence: 0.90
        }
    ]
    
    Note: Only customers with GroupID returned
    (Customers without associations are filtered out)
end note

:Filter: Where GroupID.HasValue;

note right
    In code:
    assDetectionHasGroupID = 
        DetectAssociation(...)?
            .Where(n => n.GroupID.HasValue);
    
    Only customers in groups are considered fraud
    Individual bettors (no association) are skipped
end note

stop

floating note right
    ===============================================================
    ASSOCIATION DETECTION SUMMARY
    ===============================================================
    
    **Purpose:**
    Identify groups of customers betting together (fraud detection)
    
    **Methods (5 criteria):**
    1. ✓ Device Detection - Same device ID
    2. ✓ AI Detection - ML pattern matching
    3. ✓ IP Detection - Same IP address
    4. ✓ 3 Matches Last 7 Days - Frequent co-betting
    5. ✓ IP Last 3 Days - Recent IP matching
    
    **Sport-Specific:**
    Each sport can enable/disable criteria independently
    Example: Soccer uses all 5, Basketball only Device+IP
    
    **Flexible Configuration:**
    - API parameters control which sports use which criteria
    - Easy to adjust per sport without code changes
    - Can add new criteria without breaking existing
    
    **Performance:**
    - Single SP call for all detections
    - Efficient grouping algorithm
    - Results cached for reuse
    
    **Output:**
    - GroupID: Unique group identifier
    - AssociationType: Which method(s) detected
    - Confidence: Detection confidence score (if applicable)
    
    **Integration:**
    Used by:
    - Group Betting Rule (Match Monitor)
    - Association Detection Reports
    - Customer Classification
    - Fraud Investigation Tools
end note

@enduml

